{{short description|Mountain in Saudi Arabia}} {{Refimprove| date= October 2017}} {{Infobox mountain | name = Jabal Sawda | photo = Al Sawda peak.jpg | photo_caption = | elevation = Around {{convert|3000|m|ft|0}}. | prominence_m = | prominence_ref= | range = [[Hejaz Mountains]] | listing = | map = Saudi Arabia | map_caption = | label_position = right | location = [[Saudi Arabia]] | coordinates = {{coord|18|16|02|N|42|22|05|E|type:mountain_region:SA_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }} '''Jabal Sawda''' ({{lang-ar|جبل السودة}} ''{{transl|ar|ALA-LC|jabal al-sūda}}'', {{IPA-ar|dʒabal asːuːda|pron}})is a peak located in [[Saudi Arabia]], with an elevation of around {{convert|3000|m|ft|0}}.
Most authorities claim that the peak, with a questioned elevation of 3,133 m, is the highest point in Saudi Arabia, but [[Shuttle Radar Topography Mission|SRTM]] data indicates an elevation of 2,985 m, with higher elevations elsewhere in the country.
Also known as Mount Souda in Abha (جبل السودة في ابها) is a [[mountain]] of [[Saudi Arabia]], located in the [[Hejaz Mountains]] at Coordinates 18°16'02"[[north|N]] and 42°22'05"[[east|E]].
The village of [[Al Souda]] is located nearby. That town is a tourist center and has a [[Aerial lift|cable car]] to the top of the mountain.<ref>https://www.tripadvisor.com.au/ShowUserReviews-g298542-d7084575-r292681756-Cable_Car-Abha_Asir_Province.html</ref>
